'''''lond''''' or '''''lonn''''' is a [[Sindarin]] noun meaning "land-locked haven".<ref>{{S|Appendix}}, entry ''[[londë]]''</ref> The [[Noldorin]] form was '''''lhonn''''', meaning "narrow path, strait, pass".<ref>{{LR|Etymologies}}, entries "[[AK]]", "LOD"</ref>

==Examples==
* ''[[Aglon|Ag'''lon''']]'' = "Narrow Pass"
* ''[[Edhellond|Edhel'''lond''']]'' = "Elf Haven"
* ''[[Forlond|For'''lond''']]'' = "North Haven"
* ''[[Lond Daer|'''Lond''' Daer]]'' = "Great Haven"
* ''[[Mithlond|Mith'''lond''']]'' = "Foggy (Grey) Havens"

==Cognates==
*[[Quenya]] ''[[londë]]''
